      <h1 class='title'>Missing Persons</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 cc256-7WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_256ws' title='Col. 256WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c256WS' name='column_256ws' href='#column_256ws' rel='bookmark'>256WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06226'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_241'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-paul-marsden' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_241' title='Link to this speech by Mr Paul Marsden' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-paul-marsden" title="Mr Paul Marsden">Mr. Paul Marsden</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06226">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what plans he has to introduce a common reporting procedure for police services for missing persons. [88190]</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_257ws' title='Col. 257WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c257WS' name='column_257ws' href='#column_257ws' rel='bookmark'>257WS</a>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06227'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_242'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-denham' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_242' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Denham' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-denham" title="Mr John Denham">Mr. Denham</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06227">There is an agreed procedure: details of all missing persons should be recorded on the Police National Computer (PNC) as soon as possible and in any case within 48 hours of their disappearance.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06228">Notification of all outstanding missing persons should be sent to the Police National Missing Persons Bureau (PNMPB), based at New Scotland Yard, within 14 days. Most missing persons are found locally within this period. Forces will not, however, be precluded from forwarding information to the PNMPB in a shorter time if a particular case appears to warrant more urgent attention.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06229">Details of unidentified persons or bodies found should be reported to the PNMPB within 48 hours of being found.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
